ZH: 我的父亲在生前立了一份详细的遗嘱。
EN: My father left a detailed will before he passed away.
ZH: 他遵守了他祖父的遗嘱，并将家产传给了他的孩子们。
EN: He followed his grandfather's will and passed on the family fortune to his children.
ZH: 执行遗嘱的人应该是个可信任的人。
EN: The executor of a will should be someone trustworthy.
ZH: 这份遗嘱规定了我的全部财产应该分配给我的子女。
EN: This will stipulates that all my assets should be distributed to my children.
ZH: 她没有遗嘱，因此她的财产将由法庭来决定如何分配。
EN: She didn't have a will, so her assets will be distributed by the court.
ZH: 如有必要，我会修改我的遗嘱以反映我的最新意愿。
EN: If necessary, I will amend my will to reflect my latest wishes.
ZH: 我母亲在她的遗嘱中表达了她对家人的深深爱意。
EN: My mother expressed her deep love for her family in her will.
ZH: 遗嘱是确保我的遗产按照我所希望的方式进行分配的保证。
EN: A will is the assurance that my estate will be distributed according to my wishes.
ZH: 在我离世之后，请确保我的遗嘱得到遵守。
EN: Please ensure that my will is followed after I pass away.
ZH: 制定遗嘱是保护我的家人和财产的一种方式。
EN: Making a will is a way to protect my family and assets.
ZH: 遗嘱可以帮助避免亲戚之间的争议和纷争。
EN: A will can help avoid disputes and conflicts among relatives.
ZH: 遗嘱执行人的职责是确保遗嘱得到有效执行。
EN: The executor's duty is to ensure the will is executed properly.
ZH: 它是我明确表达我对财产分配的方式的遗嘱。
EN: It is my will that clearly expresses how my assets should be distributed.
ZH: 每个人都应该准备一份遗嘱，无论年龄或财务状况如何。
EN: Everyone should have a will prepared, regardless of age or financial status.
ZH: 我要保证我的遗嘱始终是最新的，以反映我的真实意愿。
EN: I want to ensure that my will is always up to date to reflect my true intentions.
ZH: 遗嘱的内容受到法律的保护，应该按照法律进行执行。
EN: The contents of a will are protected by law and should be executed according to legal procedures.
ZH: 遗嘱执行人应该有责任保护遗嘱的完整性和有效性。
EN: The executor has the responsibility to protect the integrity and validity of the will.
ZH: 我的祖父留下了一份详细的遗嘱，规定了他整个财产将由他的儿子继承。
EN: My grandfather left a detailed will that stipulated his entire estate would be inherited by his son.
ZH: 遗嘱需要在见证人的面前签署和公证。
EN: A will needs to be signed and notarized in the presence of witnesses.
ZH: 按照遗嘱，我的房子要传给我的孙子。
EN: According to the will, my house is to be passed on to my grandson.
